                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If the Chanter charm dps is to be lowered to that of a mage pet of comparable level, then risk should be the same as a mage; ie, zero.  A charmed pet should have no brks unless the chanter dies, zones or tells the pet to go away.   
<br />

<br />
If we cant have the reward -- why have the risk.
<br />

<br />
Lets not settle as a community for a token agro reducer such as an upgraded boggle.  This change to charm Damage does not look like it will be reversed.  So we should work on the Risk aspect.  We should be prepared for this damage change to be applied to all levels of charm.  We need to as a community get behind one front and that is the Risk aspect and not back down from demanding a fair and equitable solution to this problem.  As I have stated:  If Damage = mage pet then Risk = Mage risk.
<br />

<br />
One more point:
<br />

<br />
Nanyea has stated that the damage is scalable.  If this change begins to apply outside Omens then a level 65 chanter charming a level 50 mob should get a pet = to a level 65 mage's pet,  not a weak level 50 pet.
<br />

<br />
IE the Dmg of a charmed pet should equal the dmg of a mage pet = not to the level of the charmed pet but to the level of the chanter.
<br />

<br />
Also unlock all mobs--make everything charmable again.
<br />

<br />
We need to find a clear course for the devs and we need to do this fast</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
