                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is a simple risk vs reward argument.  It doesn't matter if you are using a mage pet as the example, or the DPS of any other class, or the average DPS of all classes as an example.
<br />

<br />
The only significant DPS contribution enchanters have is via charm.  If charm is modified so its DPS output is only going to be basically the same as everyone else's DPS, except at random intervals our DPS is going to suddenly stop working for us and then instantly double and start kicking the crap out of our group, then that is a fundamental problem with the risk vs reward equation.
<br />

<br />
The devs don't seem to care about this, and arguably some of the enchanters don't seem to care about this either.  But, it is reality regardless of which side of the fence you sit on.  There is an obvious perception among the devs, and even the EQ community at large, that charm was overpowered.  This was the 'solution' they came up with, and it really wasn't very well thought out.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
