                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Comparing it to another class' ability like this is completely invalid. Classes get abilities in relation to the design goal of the class and to how it fits (balancewise) with their other abilities. Pets are absolutely fundamental to the Mage, not to the enchanter. You can't just say, since we can charm, it should be the same risk/reward. By that rationale all druid heals should equal cleric heals, all slows should equal shaman slows, etc..
<br />

<br />
Do I think the dev's went a bit overboard with the charm nerf? Yes. But I do agree with both the method and goal. Charm <span style="font-style: italic">should</span> be wider useable, and definately more situational. Not a permanent and overpowered DPS tool. PoP charm reward/risk was out of whack if the player had half a clue.
<br />

<br />
All in all, I see OoW as more of a boon than a nerf to us. Our spells are not the greatest, and charm is less usefull, but our AA's seem among the best, and far more importantly, the content is far more taylored to us. I've cast more mez's during this week, than I have during the past 2 months. Wandering adds are great. And everything I've seen so far can be manatapped. I still wonder if the last one is bug though.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
