                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In case you haven't figured it out yer, Enchanters are tohught of as a support classby the developers. The fact that we add DPSis incidental to what are main function is in the grand sheme of things, ie, class balancing.
<br />

<br />
Having said that, we still add significant DPS to a group. Starting with nuking, Insanity, being chain cast over the course of a fight can add around 200 DPS to the groups damage output. My anination adds about 30 dps. That works out to 180 per tick, 20 less than Saryrn's Kiss(lvl 62 Necro dot). Once cast, the animation is essentially a manaless dot. If I have a DC pet that adds around 150 DPS in zpnes like Sol Ro'sd Tower or Earth. Unless I'm in OOW, any charmed pet i have still does fine damage. Pooks still hit for 1048 and do great damage. A group I was in the other day took out the named in Tipt un under 15 secs, it might not have been much more than 10. The group consisted of My chanter, a Zerker, Bard, Warrior, CLeric and a Shammy. Not exactly what you would call a heavy DPS group. I guarantee the Pooka did 3/4 of the damage in that fight.
<br />

<br />
Posts such as the one that started this thread annoy me. Comparing Mages to Chanters is like comparing Clerics to Druids Both can heal but their roles in a group are dramatically different. Magesm perhaps more than any other class, are defined by thier pets. Take away a Mages pet and you cripple thier ability to contribute to a group. Take away a Chanter's ability to Charm and we still can do most of what we are expected to do.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Starmist
<br />
Alliance of Hope
