                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Crowd control (via mez) is dead and has been since Kunark.  A few events (HP and Emp in Ssra, Rathe Council, etc) do not make it important enough to have mez be the specialty of one class.  The approach of designing zones and content has been to decrease the number of mobs, while increasing their HP and DPS.  Part of this is necessary due to server demands (see statement regarding change to Bard DoTs eliminating DoT kiting).  Root is a form of crowd control available to most pure casters and even some hybrids.  Snare + agro kite is also available.  Mez simply is not needed.  
<br />

<br />
We also had buffs.  Increased self mana regen for all casters, stacking mana regen via Po9, SD, and Bard song, and duration of C3 minimize (actually effectively eliminate) the need for Clarity line in casters in single groups.  The item+spell haste cap has held fast at 100 pct, while other classes' (Shaman, Beastlords, and Bards) haste lines have increased to nearly match our own, and items with self-buff haste spells have become more widely available in the game.  The poor mana-hp ratio of Runes, the fact that our best can be taken down with one hit, and the Peridot component cost make them pretty much a raid-only tool.  Other classes have been given melee/spell mitigation  (B. of Vie, Spellshield) make runes even less of a necessity on raids.
<br />

<br />
What is left for us to do?  Charm.  SoE created the situation.  It's up to them to fix it while maintaining our class usefulness to groups and raids.  The latest charm adjustment is insane when taken in context with the above.
<br />

<br />
While I think its useless to compare us directly to a Mage, a Necro, a Shaman, or any other class - it does make sense to look at our core abilities and compare / contrast them with all other classes as a whole.
<br />

<br />
Duoing named in Tactics is fun.  Soloing is fun (and becoming the primary experience grind alternative to grouping).  I don't mind giving them up in OoW.  I just want to contribute more than a few atk (SoV vs Talisman of Alacrity) and few mana regen points (C5 vs C3) and a 2 to 3K nuke potential per kill.
<br />

<br />
How can charm be useful without overpowering (as it is in a few PoP zones)?  Make everything summon and immune to stun - eliminates pet tanking.  The movement speed of mobs in OoW as it is effectively minimizes snare.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Nokei Orhaste</a></span>
<br />
Coercer for <span style="color: blue"><a href="http://www.houseofaegis.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">House of Aegis</a></span>
