                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">While I am not real pleased with the change to charm in OoW, I can't seem to understand where this idea that our pets are lowered to a mage pet. I have only charmed once for a decent long duration in an OoW zone (instanced zone Catacombs off Ruined City of Dranik) and that mob was still hitting for 230 a pop while charmed. Can mage pets do this?
<br />

<br />
And as for mez not being useable, I was in Wall of Slaughter and held 3 mobs locked down just fine while the cleric rezzed the people that got killed by the train, rebuffed them, then killed all the mobs. Isn't that what we do?
<br />

<br />
Again, not happy with the charm change, not happy with the linking of spells on the timer, and still pissed about the blow off we got about tash aggro versus malo aggro (FOAD everyone at SOE involved in that decision), but lets not describe the existing situation to be worse than it really is.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
