                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Again, just my opinion, when SoE talks to us they tend to put things in a total context.  They will use comparisons of one class to others, one class's abilities to the abilities of another class.  They are not comparing us to other class's they are giving us a context for why they did/do what they did. 
<br />
 
<br />
When we compare ourselves to a specific class, class ability then we are essentially doing nothing more than engaging in class envy.  That may not be the purpose but that is certainly how it will be viewed. 
<br />
 
<br />
One could pursue this along this line. 
<br />
 
<br />
With the risk of a charmed pet turning on us after it breaks our charm, then killing us, why is the DPS output of said charmed pet set equal to a summoned pet? 
<br />
 
<br />
In my opinion, the above does not focus on class's it focus's on your issue.  If a charmer takes the risk of charming a pet then that pet should be better than a summoned pet. 
<br />
 
<br />
No it does not follow that a charmed level 1 pet should be equal to a summoned level 65 pet. 
<br />
 
<br />
It does follow that a charmed level 65 pet should be better than a summoned level 65 pet or the aggro should be totaly removed.  Said more simply the risk of charming should be removed if the charmed pet is <span style="font-weight: bold">intentionally</span> reduced in abilility to correspond to a summoned pet of the same level.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Morpheus to Neo, "Remember -- all I am offering is the truth, nothing more." 
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v159/EnigmaJL/avatar3.png" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
